article.description: — DaRon Holmes scored 18 points to lead Dayton to a 72-52 win over Duquesne on Saturday.
article.headline: Holmes scores 18, Elvis 16 in Dayton's win over Duquesne
article.linkText: Holmes scores 18, Elvis 16 in Dayton's win over Duquesne
article.story: PITTSBURGH -- — DaRon Holmes scored 18 points to lead Dayton to a 72-52 win over Duquesne on Saturday. Kobe Elvis added 16 for the Flyers (11-6, 3-1 Atlantic 10). Tre Williams, Primo Spears and Leon Ayers III scored 12 points apiece for Duquesne (6-9, 1-2) with Kevin Easley adding 10. ----
